title: The Middle East crisis is stirring up a 'tsunami' of mental health woes
description: The Israel-Gaza conflict is likely to leave people in the region struggling with trauma-related mental health symptoms for a long time to come.

title: Siding with Trump, the ACLU says a judge's gag order in Jan. 6 case is too sweeping
description: The ACLU says a judge's gag order against former President Trump restricts too much of his speech on matters of public importance.

title: Facing dementia without a diagnosis is crushing. A new program in Kenya offers help
description: In Kenya, someone with symptoms of dementia may not be able to get a diagnosis — leaving both patient and family with no idea of what is going on. A program in Kenya is trying to change that.
